ArduFlipper one pins .

Because the OLED display uses I2C communication protocol, wiring is very simple. You just need to connect to the Arduino Uno I2C pins as shown in the table below.

oled - Pins Arduino 
( note if your oled has other adress then 0X3C , change display.begin(SSD1306_SWITCHCAPVCC, 0x3C);  in Arduino sketch to correct i2c adress

/////////////////////
Vin	     5V
GND	     GND
SCL	     A5
SDA	     A4
////////////////


Joystick Module  
Module - Arduino pins
/////////////////////////
Vin      5v
GND      GND
SW       5
VERT     A0
HORIZ    A!
/////////////////////////

(NOTE ! in EU whe use 433 Mhz and in US 315 , for the tesla charge port ! ) 
buy the one you think you wil use the most in your country )

Pin wiring 433 Mhz Rx Module 
Module - Arduino pins
/////////////////////////
Vin      5v
Data     3
GND      GND
/////////////////////////

Pin wiring 433 Mhz Tx Module 
Module - Arduino pins
/////////////////////////
Vin      5v
Data     2
GND      GND
/////////////////////////


